<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733817FF4DFCFDFD94FC8C" box="[136,593,819,845]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FF4DFCFDFD94FC8C" blockId="546.[136,593,819,845]" box="[136,593,819,845]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<heading id="D09A81B1ED733817FF4DFCFDFD94FC8C" bold="true" box="[136,593,819,845]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF4DFCFDFD94FC8C" bold="true" box="[136,593,819,845]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FF1AFCFDFD94FC8C" authority="Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[223,593,819,845]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF1AFCFDFE93FC8C" bold="true" box="[223,342,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Demoixys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED733817FE9BFCFDFD94FC8C" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[350,593,819,845]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733817FF4DFCB9FD30FA34" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FF4DFCB9FD30FA34" blockId="546.[136,778,887,2002]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF4DFCB9FF3EFC50" bold="true" box="[136,251,887,913]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body globular or stout. Dorsal cephalic shield with or without horn-like posterolateral processes. Free urosome small, 2- to 5-segmented. Caudalramus small, poorly defined from anal somite; caudal setae at most 
<quantity id="4C959B38ED733817FD25FC13FCCFFC36" box="[736,778,989,1016]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
number or apparently absent. Rostrum distinct.Antennule small, unsegmented or at most 6-segmented.Antenna 3- or 4-segmented, with small terminal claw. Mandible bearing 3 to 6 teeth on coxal gnathobase; armed with 1 seta on basis, 2 to 5 on exopod, and at most 6 on 1- or 2-segmented endopod. Maxillule as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FE70FB64FDDEFB02" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[437,539,1194,1219]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FE70FB64FDDEFB02" box="[437,539,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or much reduced to bilobed appendage; coxal epipodite usually present, but coxal endite absent. Maxilla 3- or 4-segmented; syncoxa with 3 endites at most; basis withlarge claw; endopod 1- or 2-segmented, armed with total of 4 setae at most. Maxilliped as small lobe bearing 2 to 6 setae. Legs 1–4 variously reduced, weak, consistingof indistinctly 2- segmented rami, or further reduced to 2 small lobes or rudimentary knob. Leg 5 absent, or represented by outer lobe and tapering inner process, or represented by lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733817FF78FA30FE1DF9F8" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FF78FA30FE1DF9F8" blockId="546.[136,778,887,2002]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF78FA30FE9CF9D6" bold="true" box="[189,345,1533,1560]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED733817FF78FA30FF3DF9D9" box="[189,248,1534,1560]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FEB5FA30FF07F9F8" authority="Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chattoni">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FEB5FA30FD8CF9D6" box="[368,585,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Demoixys chattoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED733817FD9DFA33FF07F9F8" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733817FF78F98CFF3DF813" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FF78F98CFF3DF813" blockId="546.[136,778,887,2002]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF78F98CFEEFF99D" bold="true" box="[189,298,1602,1628]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Remarks</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FE7DF98CFDE3F99A" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[440,550,1602,1627]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FE7DF98CFDE3F99A" box="[440,550,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Demoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was poorly defined in the original report of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED733817FE05F9ADFD0CF9BF" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[448,713,1635,1662]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FED733817FDD8F9ADFDAAF9BC" box="[541,623,1635,1661]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Dudley</collectingRegion>
(1961)
</bibRefCitation>
who differentiated between it and other notodelphyids by its weakly segmented, inflated body, its reduced antennular segmentation, and the highly modified mouthparts and legs. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FDD4F922FDBCF8C4" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1965" box="[529,633,1772,1797]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mesoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FDD4F922FDBCF8C4" box="[529,633,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Mesoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the form of the mandible (which has a styliform coxal gnathobase in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FF6CF8FEFED4F888" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1965" box="[169,273,1840,1865]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mesoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF6CF8FEFED4F888" box="[169,273,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Mesoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the 5-segmented maxilla (Humes &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED733817FF6AF89CFE81F8AD" author="Stock, J. H." box="[175,324,1874,1900]" journalOrPublisher="Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" pagination="1 - 45" part="123" refId="ref331120" refString="Stock, J. H. (1970) Notodelphyidae and Botryllophilidae (Copepoda) from the West Indies. Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands, 123, 1 - 45." title="Notodelphyidae and Botryllophilidae (Copepoda) from the West Indies" type="journal article" year="1970">Stock, 1970</bibRefCitation>
). It can be distinguished from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FF4DF8BAFED2F84F" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[136,279,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Lobodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FF4DF8BAFED2F84F" box="[136,279,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Lobodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED733817FE94F8BAFD66F84F" authority="Gotto, 1981" authorityName="Gotto" authorityYear="1981" box="[337,675,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Paralobodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FE94F8BAFDD5F84F" box="[337,528,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Paralobodelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED733817FDDFF8BAFD66F84F" author="Gotto, R. V." box="[538,675,1908,1934]" journalOrPublisher="Crustaceana" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" pagination="173 - 177" part="40" refId="ref328154" refString="Gotto, R. V. (1981) Paralobodelphys setipoda n. gen. n. sp. (Cyclopoida, Notodelphyidae): an ascidicolous copepod from the Great Barrier Reef, Australia. Crustaceana, 40 (2), 173 - 177. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854081 X 00570" title="Paralobodelphys setipoda n. gen. n. sp. (Cyclopoida, Notodelphyidae): an ascidicolous copepod from the Great Barrier Reef, Australia" type="journal article" year="1981">Gotto, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, because both of these genera lack a coxal gnathobase on the mandible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
